{"id":"276486176_Document_Image_Binarization_using_Local_Features_and_Gaussian_Mixture_Modelling","abstract":"In this paper, we address the document image binarization problem with a three-stage procedure. First, possible stains and general document background information are removed from the image through a background removal stage. The remaining misclassified background and character pixels are then separated using a Local Co-occurrence Mapping, local contrast and a two-state Gaussian Mixture Model. Finally, some isolated misclassified components are removed by a morphology operator. The proposed scheme offers robust and fast performance, especially for both handwritten and printed documents, which compares favourably with other binarization methods.","authors":["Nikolaos Mitianoudis","Nikos Papamarkos"],"meta":["June 2015Image and Vision Computing 38:33-51","DOI:10.1016/j.imavis.2015.04.003"],"references":["256663041_A_model_for_the_gray-intensity_distribution_of_historical_handwritten_documents_and_its_application_for_binarization","240308788_FAIR_a_Fast_Algorithm_for_Document_Image_Restoration","225529414_An_old_greek_handwritten_OCR_system_based_on_an_efficient_segmentation-free_approach","221755665_Color-to-Grayscale_Does_the_Method_Matter_in_Image_Recognition","221389513_H-DIBCO_2010_-_Handwritten_Document_Image_Binarization_Competition","220933012_Binarization_of_historical_document_images_using_the_local_maximum_and_minimum","220860516_ICDAR_2009_Document_Image_Binarization_Contest_DIBCO_2009","220860073_ICDAR_2013_document_image_binarization_contest_DIBCO_2013","220372447_A_neuro-fuzzy_technique_for_document_binarisation","220184136_Color2Gray_Salience-preserving_color_removal","220163556_DIBCO_2009_Document_image_binarization_contest","220163435_Document_image_binarization_using_background_estimation_and_stroke_edges","3710586_Adaptive_Document_Binarization","3481053_Document_binarisation_using_Kohonen_SOM","312917987_A_gentle_tutorial_of_the_em_algorith